---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = '2025-01-01';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms of service governing the use of Longhorn Supply & Provision: research-use restrictions, prohibited uses, age and qualification requirements, Texas jurisdiction."
>
  <article class="container-rugged py-12 lg:py-16 max-w-3xl">
    <p class="font-display uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-copper text-xs mb-1">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-ink">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-charcoal/60">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="prose max-w-none mt-8 text-charcoal leading-relaxed space-y-5">
      <p class="text-sm text-charcoal/70 border-l-2 border-copper pl-3">
        These Terms are provided as a starting template. Before launching the site, have these reviewed by an attorney licensed in your jurisdiction with experience in the research-chemical and consumer-products industries.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing or using the Longhorn Supply &amp; Provision website (the "Site") or purchasing any product from us, you ("Customer", "you") agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree, do not use the Site or purchase any product.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">2. Research Use Only</h2>
      <p>
        All products offered on this Site are sold <strong>for laboratory and research use only</strong>. They are <strong>not</strong> intended for human or animal consumption; for use in food or food additives; for diagnostic, therapeutic, cosmetic, or veterinary purposes; or for use in or on the human body. Products are not approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration and are not drugs, supplements, or medical devices.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">3. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>
        You represent and warrant that you are (a) at least 21 years of age, (b) a qualified researcher, laboratory professional, or institutional purchaser acting in such capacity, (c) lawfully able to purchase research chemicals in your jurisdiction, and (d) located in the United States.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">4. Prohibited Uses</h2>
      <p>
        You agree that you will <strong>not</strong>: (a) consume, ingest, inhale, inject, or otherwise administer any product to yourself, another human, or an animal; (b) re-sell, redistribute, or repackage products for human or animal consumption; (c) misrepresent any product as a drug, supplement, food, or medical device; (d) export products outside the United States; or (e) use products in any manner that violates federal, state, or local law.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">5. No Medical Claims</h2>
      <p>
        We make no medical, therapeutic, prophylactic, diagnostic, or nutritional claims regarding any product. Nothing on the Site is medical advice. Statements about a compound's research applications describe published in vitro or animal-model literature; they are not statements about effects in humans.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">6. Orders, Pricing, and Quotes</h2>
      <p>
        Prices are quoted on request and are subject to change without notice. Submission of a quote request does not constitute an order. An order is created only after we confirm pricing, availability, payment, and shipping details in writing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">7. Shipping &amp; Returns</h2>
      <p>
        Shipping is limited to the continental United States. Returns of opened, reconstituted, or altered products are not accepted. See our <a href="/shipping" class="text-copper underline">Shipping &amp; Returns</a> page for full terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        Products are provided "as is" without warranty of any kind beyond the published specification on the applicable Certificate of Analysis. To the maximum extent permitted by law, Longhorn Supply &amp; Provision, its owners, officers, employees, and affiliates shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from purchase or use of any product, including any unauthorized administration to a human or animal.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">9. Indemnification</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Longhorn Supply &amp; Provision against any claims, damages, losses, or expenses arising from your breach of these Terms, including any use of a product in violation of Section 4 (Prohibited Uses).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">10. Governing Law &amp; Jurisdiction</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to its conflict-of-laws principles. Exclusive venue for any dispute is the state or federal courts located in Texas. The parties waive any right to a jury trial.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">11. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Updated Terms are effective upon posting. Continued use of the Site after a posted update constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-ink font-display uppercase tracking-tight mt-8 text-2xl">12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:legal@longhornsupply.com" class="text-copper underline">legal@longhornsupply.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
